title: For Sale:  Enfield No.1 Mark III and Bayonet
postcontent: Enfield No.1 Mark III 303 British year of manufacture is 1915 and Bayonet manufactured in 1907. The best I can tell all the serial numbers match including the receiver, bolt and the bayonet mount. I could not see any other serial numbers on any other parts of the rifle. About 8 years ago I purchased this Rifle at Joe’s sporting goods before they went out of business. This is a surplus Rifle and shows typical wear indicative of these types of Rifles with dings, dents, scratches etc. This Rifle is marked GF (Grenade Firing) and at some point in time a bolt was put through the stock to strengthen it to fire grenades. These Rifles would usually have coper wrapped around the stock however this ones coper is gone and you can see the imprints and marks from where the coper used to be. The bore looks pretty good it is a slightly dull and not super bright. I have fired this Rifle and it operated very well and was surprisingly accurate despite how the bore looks. I also have a Bayonet that I am selling with this Rifle. This is the correct Bayonet for this Rifle and snaps right on the end of the Rifle with no problem. Overall I would say that the Bayonet is in very nice condition and I have not cleaned it so I have not taken away any of its original patina. The blade appears to have never been sharpened and there are 5 nicks in the blade that are most likely from combat use. It has the original Scabbard that is in great condition as well. *Please note that I will only sell through a reputable FFL with a license number that I can verify. I prefer to sell Face to Face however I will ship Firearms and sell outside of the State of Washington. This will cost an additional $80 and that covers Shipping, paper work done by my FFL and the Sales Tax Washington State charges. In the case of shipping a Firearm the only form of payment I accept is via PayPal*
